<PageLayout title='About' {headings} info='/about'>
  <p>Web3 Developer / Security Researcher</p>
  <p>Hi, I’m Shashank — a curious mind exploring the intersection of cybersecurity, blockchain, and software engineering.</p>

  <p>I’m an undergraduate computer science student with a growing focus on cybersecurity—especially cryptography and capture-the-flag (CTF) challenges. I actively compete with bi0s, one of India’s top CTF teams, where I sharpen my skills through real-world problem solving and hands-on exploration.</p>
    
  <p>I’m especially passionate about decentralization and Web3. Working with smart contracts and building dApps allows me to merge security-focused thinking with the creativity of software development—an intersection I find endlessly exciting.</p>
    
  <p>Outside the terminal, you’ll often find me deep in a book or admiring mechanical watches. I enjoy quirky reads like How to Lie with Statistics—because even numbers can bend the truth without context.</p>
    
  <p>I don’t claim to know everything. I just believe in asking better questions every day.</p> <Spoiler>Stay hungry, stay foolish.</Spoiler>
   
    
  
  

